# Pearl store runtime files — keep the dolt manifest + content-
# addressed blobs in git (so pearls sync between machines via git
# push/pull), but exclude anything ephemeral.

# Per-process lock files
*/.dolt/noms/LOCK

# Temp / scratch dirs
*/.dolt/temptf/
*/.dolt/noms/.temptf/

# Stats engine sidecar (rebuilt on demand)
*/.dolt/stats/

# Dolt's git-style remote object cache — rebuilt on demand by
# `th pearls push/pull`. Was historically tracked, which made every
# sync produce hundreds of noisy index changes. Untracked + ignored.
*/.dolt/git-remote-cache/

# Transient noms manifest temp files. Dolt usually cleans these up
# but doesn't always — gitignore so they don't show as `??`.
*/.dolt/noms/nbs_manifest_*
